Regrettable_Termination.description: Boolean attribute identifying whether the termination was regrettable.

Rehire.description: Returns "Yes" if the worker is a rehire based on the most recent hire event.

Related_Person.description: Contains the dependent, beneficiary, and emergency contact information for the related person.

Resignation_Date.description: Date the employee submitted their resignation.

Retired.description: Boolean attribute identifying whether the Worker is currently retired.

Retirement_Eligibility_Date.description: Retirement Eligibility Date for the Worker.

Return_Benefits_as_of_Payment_Date_Promp.description: Boolean attribute to signify whether the response data for Benefit Plan Data (within Deduction Data) should include Benefit Elections as of the Period Payment Date instead of the Period End Date.

Return_Unknown.description: Returns "Yes" if it is unknown if the Canadian worker is expected to return as specified on the most recent termination transaction. This field is specific to Canadian employment.

Seniority_Date.description: Seniority date for the worker.  Defaults to hire date.

Simplified_View.description: To enable user preferences that simplify the overall user experience.

Terminated.description: Boolean attribute identifying whether the Worker is currently Terminated.

Termination_Involuntary.description: Indicates if the termination was involuntary.

Termination_Last_Day_of_Work.description: Last day worked for the worker's termination event.

Time_Off_Service_Date.description: The Time Off Service Date in the worker's service dates. If empty, Workday will use the existing date.

Time_Zone_Reference_Time_Zone_ID.description: Contains a unique identifier for an instance of an object.

Time_Zone_Reference_WID.description: Contains a unique identifier for an instance of an object.

Tobacco_Use.description: True if the person uses tobacco.  To update a person's Tobacco Use, use the Put Worker Wellness Data web service.

Universal_ID.description: The universal ID uniquely identifies the Person. It remains the same for a person regardless of what roles they have.  This field will be automatically populated if a sequence generator is configured in Edit Tenant Setup-System.

Universal_ID_Reference_Universal_Identif.description: The universal identifier of the payees.  All payee roles will be returned for a given universal identifier.. Supports multiple values.

Universal_ID_Reference_WID_Prompt.description: The universal identifier of the payees.  All payee roles will be returned for a given universal identifier.. Supports multiple values.

Universal_Identifier_Reference_Universal.description: Contains a unique identifier for an instance of an object.

Universal_Identifier_Reference_WID.description: Contains a unique identifier for an instance of an object.

Use_Pay_Period_for_Payroll_Input_Start_a.description: When enabled, this option will use the respective Pay Period for Payroll Input Start and End Dates. This replaces the current behavior of using the Begin Entry Moment specified in the Response Date Range Filter to derive the period.

Use_Pay_Period_for_Time_Off_Period_Start.description: Used to indicate that the Pay Period Start and End dates should be used for Time Off entry selection.

User_Language__Reference_User_Language_I.description: Contains a unique identifier for an instance of an object.

User_Language__Reference_WID.description: Contains a unique identifier for an instance of an object.

User_Name.description: The user name that is used to sign on to the Workday application.

Vesting_Date.description: The Vesting Date in the employee's service dates. If empty, Workday will use the existing date.

Visa_ID.description: Wrapper element for all Visa Identifier Data.

Work_Experience.description: Wrapper element for the work experience.
